The WannaCry ransomware attack in 2017, which affected over 200,000 organizations across 150 countries, including hospitals, banks, and government agencies.
The SolarWinds cyber attack in 2020, which impacted multiple government agencies and major companies, including the Department of Homeland Security, the Department of Energy, and Microsoft.
The Yahoo data breach in 2013, which exposed the personal information of over 3 billion user accounts, making it the largest data breach in history.
The Equifax data breach in 2017, which exposed the personal information of over 147 million individuals, including social security numbers and credit card numbers.
The Marriott data breach in 2018, which exposed the personal information of over 500 million guests, including credit card numbers and passport numbers.
